The paper focuses on improving the training of deep neural networks for computer vision problems, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of various gradient update methods, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces new techniques for improving convergence and analyzing the loss surface, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of these techniques for classification, detection, and segmentation, which suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category, as it discusses the use of deep neural networks for segmentation tasks.
